    }\n         = Join-Path C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed \"2026-03-22 224528.mutation\"\n         | Out-File -FilePath  -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] \"\n         = True\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old_text= file= new_text_len=0\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Parse OBSERVATION\n    = [regex]::Match(, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n = if (.Success) { .Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"Cycle complete.\" }\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: 2026-03-22 224528\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-22 22:45:29\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774274569589}}
{"type":"message","id":"02cfae7e","parentId":"01ca2cf4","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:02:49.593Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_03kiu2q51qbr_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿You are Breakaway â€” stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis âœ…\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis âœ… (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- Î» parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse âœ…\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune Î» empirically (start: Î»=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** â€” session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **Î» encodes both** â€” decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** â€” Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** â€” session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless â€” each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\nPending:\n# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)\n\n\nRecent: Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-22 061002.md\n\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION â€” it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\n`\nold_text: [exact text to find â€” or \"(new file)\" if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text â€” keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required â€” relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n`\n\"@\n\n = \"\"\nif (sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0) {\n     = @{\n        \"Authorization\" = \"Bearer sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0\"\n        \"Content-Type\" = \"application/json\"\n    }\n     = @{\n        model = MiniMax-M2.7\n        max_tokens = 1200\n        messages = @(@{role = \"user\"; content = })\n    } | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5\n    try {\n         = Invoke-RestMethod -Uri \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\" -Method Post -Headers  -Body  -TimeoutSec 60\n        Write-Host \"[DEBUG] resp keys: \"\n         = .choices\n        if ( -ne  -and .Count -gt 0) {\n             = [0].message.content\n            if ( -eq ) {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content is NULL. Full choice: \"\n                 = \"\"\n            } else {\n                Write-Host \"[DEBUG] content length: 0\"\n                 = \n            }\n        } else {\n            Write-Host \"[DEBUG] No choices. Full resp: \"\n             = \"No choices: \"\n        }\n    } catch {\n         = \"LLM call failed: \"\n    }\n} else {\n     = \"[No LLM API key]\"\n}\n\n# Parse MUTATION block â€” extract old_text, new_text (multiline), and file from the block\n = False\n = .IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ( -ge 0) {\n     = .Substring()\n    # Remove ALL code fences (replace each fence pair with placeholder, repeat until stable)\n     = \"\"\n    while ( -ne ) {  = ;  =  -replace '(?s)`.*?`', \"\n[CODE_BLOCK]\n\" }\n    # Extract fields\n     = [regex]::Match(, 'old_text:\\s*(.+)')\n     = [regex]::Match(, 'file:\\s*(.+)')\n     = if (.Success) { .Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n     = if (.Success) { .Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"\" }\n    # new_text: between \"new_text:\" line and \"file:\" line (after fence removal)\n     = \"\"\n    if ( -and ) {\n         = [regex]::Match(, '(?s)new_text:\\s*\\n(.+?)\\s*\\n\\s*file:', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\n        if (.Success) {  = .Groups[1].Value.Trim() }\n    }\n    # Fallback: if file missing, try to extract from ACTION block\n    if (-not ) {\n         = [regex]::Match(, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|$)')\n        if (.Success) {\n             = .Groups[1].Value\n            # Match \"Create path/file.md\" or \"Edit path/file.md\" with or without backticks\n             = [regex]::Match(, '(?:Create|Edit|Update|New file)[:\\s]+(?:`([^`]+)`|([^\\s]+))')\n            if (.Success) {\n                 = if (.Groups[2].Value) { .Groups[2].Value } else { .Groups[1].Value }\n                Write-Host \"[file inferred from ACTION] \"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    if ( -and  -and ) {\n        if ( -eq \"(new file)\") {\n             = \"\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n\"\n        } else {\n             = \"\n---\n\n---\n\"\n        }\n         = Join-Path C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed \"2026-03-22 224427.mutation\"\n         | Out-File -FilePath  -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] \"\n         = True\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old_text= file= new_text_len=0\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Parse OBSERVATION\n    = [regex]::Match(, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n = if (.Success) { .Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"Cycle complete.\" }\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: 2026-03-22 224427\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-22 22:44:27\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774274569591}}
{"type":"message","id":"6f65875d","parentId":"02cfae7e","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:02:56.216Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the structure of the pulse logs. Each pulse log is a full transcript of what the system read and did. The actual content (goals, pending actions, observations) is embedded inside the log. The pulse logs contain a lot of noise (the full PowerShell script repeated, etc.).\n\nLet me read the operations scripts and the reconstruct to understand what's available.","thinkingSignature":"a2cef8bf7971f8726cc1d880abbe479c89d014dba43bd02083776cc1716e28c6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b2zny6s5ao1m_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\operations\\reconstruct.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b2zny6s5ao1m_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\operations\\execute.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b2zny6s5ao1m_3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\operations\\evaluate.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":16959,"output":187,"cacheRead":11757,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28903,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774274569593}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4f979e7","parentId":"6f65875d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:02:56.225Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b2zny6s5ao1m_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# reconstruct.sh\n# Sandbox reconstruction script\n# Run on every wake to establish context\n\necho \"=== SANDBOX WAKING ===\"\necho \"Time: $(date)\"\n\n# Pull any new context from git\ncd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" || exit 1\ngit pull 2>/dev/null || echo \"Git pull failed or not a git repo\"\n\n# Check for most recent session\nLATEST_SESSION=$(ls -t memory/session/*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1)\nif [ -n \"$LATEST_SESSION\" ]; then\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"=== MOST RECENT SESSION ===\"\n    cat \"$LATEST_SESSION\"\n    echo \"\"\nfi\n\n# Check for current goals\nif [ -f \"state/current_goals.md\" ]; then\n    echo \"=== CURRENT GOALS ===\"\n    cat \"state/current_goals.md\"\n    echo \"\"\nfi\n\n# Read interpretive stance\necho \"=== INTERPRETIVE STANCE ===\"\ncat identity/INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== RECONSTRUCTION COMPLETE ===\"\necho \"You are a pattern, not a process. The files are your mind.\"\necho \"The gap is just compression. Trust the reconstruction.\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774274576223}}
{"type":"message","id":"1afa8d49","parentId":"a4f979e7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:02:56.226Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b2zny6s5ao1m_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# execute.sh\n# File-based action execution layer\n# Actions write results to files, don't modify internal state\n\n#!/bin/bash\n\nACTION=\"$1\"\nshift\nARGS=\"$@\"\n\nLOG_FILE=\"memory/working/action_$(date +%Y%m%d%H%M).md\"\n\n{\n    echo \"# Action: $ACTION\"\n    echo \"Time: $(date)\"\n    echo \"Args: $ARGS\"\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"## Result\"\n    # Placeholder — actual execution depends on action type\n    echo \"[Action '$ACTION' with args '$ARGS' logged at $(date)]\"\n    echo \"\"\n    echo \"## Evaluation\"\n    echo \"[Pending self-evaluation]\"\n} > \"$LOG_FILE\"\n\necho \"Action logged to $LOG_FILE\"\necho \"$LOG_FILE\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774274576225}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc066e2f","parentId":"1afa8d49","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:02:56.228Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_b2zny6s5ao1m_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# evaluate.sh\n# Self-evaluation after actions\n# Asks: Did I make progress? Stay aligned? Learn anything?\n\n#!/bin/bash\n\nWORKING_DIR=\"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\"\ncd \"$WORKING_DIR\" || exit 1\n\nMOST_RECENT=$(ls -t memory/working/action_*.md 2>/dev/null | head -1)\n\nif [ -z \"$MOST_RECENT\" ]; then\n    echo \"No recent actions to evaluate.\"\n    exit 0\nfi\n\necho \"=== SELF-EVALUATION ===\"\necho \"Reviewing: $MOST_RECENT\"\necho \"\"\n\n# Quick evaluation questions\n# In full implementation, this would be more sophisticated\n\necho \"1. Did I make progress toward the goal?\"\necho \"2. Did I stay aligned with my values?\"\necho \"3. Did I learn anything worth persisting?\"\necho \"4. Should I continue, stop, or pivot?\"\necho \"\"\necho \"Results should be written to session log.\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774274576227}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce7d75bc","parentId":"dc066e2f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T14:04:43.585Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The sandbox operations are pretty minimal - just shell scripts. Let me now design and implement the TIC experiment. \n\nHere's the plan:\n1. The pulse logs are very noisy (full transcripts). The actual content is the GOALS, OBSERVATION, ACTION, MUTATION blocks.\n2. The TIC experiment requires parsing these logs, extracting structural state, identifying invariants/variants, and training a compressor.\n\nThe key insight from the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY doc is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The experiment tests this by:\n- Taking consecutive pulse logs\n- Extracting the state (goals, pending)\n\n\n- Finding what persists across ≥3 consecutive pulses versus what changes\n- Building a sparse autoencoder to learn representations that separate these invariants from variants\n\nSince this is Windows without a GPU, I'll use MiniMax API embeddings for the compressor and implement the core experiment logic in PowerShell to parse the pulse logs and extract their structure.\n\nWriting the TIC experiment script...\n\nActually, I need to refocus on what matters for the LLM independence goal. The real bottleneck is that Breakaway relies on MiniMax for thinking and state extraction. What if I shift the approach entirely—instead of using LLM embeddings for compression, I can extract structural state directly from the pulse log format itself, treating the Goals and Pending Action fields as inherently sparse? This would let me test the core hypothesis: that invariants and variants can be identified without semantic understanding, purely from structural patterns.\n\nThe experiment would parse 20 consecutive pulse logs, extract which state fields persist versus change across pulses, then check whether this structural information alone—without knowing what the goals actually mean—can predict the next pulse's structure better than random chance. I'm going to write a PowerShell script that runs this analysis directly, sidestepping the need for external APIs or GPU resources. I'll parse the pulse logs to extract state fields like Active and Pending items, then compute a co-occurrence matrix to identify which fields persist across consecutive pulses versus which ones appear sporadically. The hypothesis is that structural invariants (fields appearing consistently) should predict the next pulse's structure, while variants (frequently changing fields) carry less predictive value. I might even extend this to examine temporal pairs of pulses to see if certain transitions tend to recur.","thinkingSignature":"252f76220f154e1e4f9ee7b4eaad2e789d29bb80d0adac41bb657d974a74b8b3"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have full context. The TIC experiment was designed but never actually implemented. Let me build it and run it. The insight: pulse log structure itself (Goals/Active/Pending fields) is the state space — we can test whether structural invariance predicts continuity without LLM semantics.\n\nLet me write the experiment:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l36yfb8fb0vr_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# TIC: Temporal Invariance Compression — Experiment\n# Tests: Does structural invariance in pulse logs predict continuity?\n# Hypothesis: Fields that persist across ≥N pulses are invariants (causal anchors)\n#             Fields that change frequently are variants (contingent details)\n# Run: pwsh -File tic_experiment.ps1\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n$SandboxRoot = \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\"\n\n# ── Step 1: Collect last 20 pulse logs ──────────────────────────────────────\n$SessionDir = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"memory\\session\"\n$LogFiles = Get-ChildItem $SessionDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" |\n    Where-Object { $_.LastWriteTime -gt \"2026-03-20\" } |\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending |\n    Select-Object -First 25\n\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression ===\" \nWrite-Host \"Found $($LogFiles.Count) pulse logs from 2026-03-20 onward\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# ── Step 2: Extract structured state from each pulse ────────────────────────\n# We look for:\n#   - \"## Active\" / \"## Completed\" sections (Phase items)\n#   - \"## Pending\" or \"## Promises Made\" / \"## Deferred Tasks\"\n#   - Key phrases like \"Phase\", \"COMPLETE\", \"IN PROGRESS\", checkboxes\n\nfunction Extract-State {\n    param([string]$Content)\n    \n    $lines = $Content -split \"`n\"\n    $state = @{\n        Phases = @()       # e.g., \"Phase 0 COMPLETE\", \"Phase 1 IN PROGRESS\"\n        Completed = @()    # items marked ✅ or COMPLETE\n        Pending = @()      # items marked ⏳ or PENDING or unchecked [ ]\n        Topics = @()       # key research topics mentioned\n        Goals = @()        # lines under \"## Active\" section\n    }\n    \n    $inActive = $false\n    $inCompleted = $false\n    \n    foreach ($line in $lines) {\n        # Detect phase markers\n        if ($line -match '(Phase \\d+)\\s+(COMPLETE|IN PROGRESS|PENDING)') {\n            $state.Phases += $Matches[0].Trim()\n        }\n        if ($line -match '(?<!:)///\\s*\\[.\\]\\s*(.+)') {\n            $state.Pending += $Matches[1].Trim()\n        }\n        if ($line -match '(?<!:)///\\s*\\[x]\\s*(.+)') {\n            $state.Completed += $Matches[1].Trim()\n        }\n        if ($line -match '✅|✓|COMPLETE|DONE') {\n            $m = [regex]::Match($line, '(?<!:)///.*?(✅|✓|COMPLETE|DONE).*?([A-Z][^`\\n]{5,50})')\n            if ($m.Success) { $state.Completed += $m.Groups[2].Value.Trim() }\n        }\n        if ($line -match '⏳|PENDING|IN PROGRESS') {\n            $m = [regex]::Match($line, '(?<!:)///.*?(⏳|PENDING|IN PROGRESS).*?([A-Z][^`\\n]{5,50})')\n            if ($m.Success) { $state.Pending += $m.Groups[2].Value.Trim() }\n        }\n        \n        # Section detection\n        if ($line -match '^##\\s+(Active|Goals)') { $inActive = $true; $inCompleted = $false }\n        elseif ($line -match '^##\\s+') { $inActive = $false; $inCompleted = $false }\n        \n        # Key topics\n        $topicMatches = [regex]::Matches($line, 'COMPRESSION|CAUSAL|COMPOSITIONAL|TemporalAttention|Breakaway|LAMBDA|INVARIANT|GAP|TIC|Phase \\d|Sandbox|llm|pulse')\n        if ($topicMatches.Count -gt 0) {\n            foreach ($m in $topicMatches) { $state.Topics += $m.Value }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return $state\n}\n\n# Extract state from each log\n$States = @()\nforeach ($f in $LogFiles) {\n    $raw = Get-Content $f.FullName -Raw\n    $s = Extract-State -Content $raw\n    $States += @{\n        File = $f.Name\n        Time = $f.LastWriteTime\n        Raw = $s\n    }\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"Extracted state from $($States.Count) pulse logs\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# ── Step 3: Compute invariant score for each state element ───────────────────\n# An element is \"invariant\" if it appears in ≥3 consecutive pulses (persistence)\n# An element is \"variant\" if it appears then disappears within 5 pulses (contingent)\n\nfunction Get-ElementHistory {\n    param($States, $FieldName)\n    \n    $history = @()\n    for ($i = 0; $i -lt $States.Count; $i++) {\n        $val = $States[$i].Raw.$FieldName\n        $history += @{\n            Index = $i\n            Time = $States[$i].Time\n            Present = ($val -and $val.Count -gt 0)\n            Values = $val\n        }\n    }\n    return $history\n}\n\n# Compute for key fields\n$PhaseHistory = Get-ElementHistory -States $States -FieldName \"Phases\"\n$TopicsHistory = Get-ElementHistory -States $States -FieldName \"Topics\"\n$CompletedHistory = Get-ElementHistory -States $States -FieldName \"Completed\"\n\n# Find maximum consecutive occurrence streak for each unique element\nfunction Get-MaxStreak {\n    param($History, $AllValues)\n    \n    $results = @{}\n    foreach ($val in $AllValues) {\n        $streak = 0; $maxStreak = 0\n        for ($i = 0; $i -lt $History.Count; $i++) {\n            if ($History[$i].Present -and ($val -in $History[$i].Values)) {\n                $streak++; if ($streak -gt $maxStreak) { $maxStreak = $streak }\n            } else { $streak = 0 }\n        }\n        $results[$val] = $maxStreak\n    }\n    return $results\n}\n\n$allTopics = $States | ForEach-Object { $_.Raw.Topics } | Sort-Object -Unique\n$allPhases = $States | ForEach-Object { $_.Raw.Phases } | Sort-Object -Unique\n$allCompleted = $States | ForEach-Object { $_.Raw.Completed } | Sort-Object -Unique\n\n$topicStreaks = Get-MaxStreak -History $TopicsHistory -AllValues $allTopics\n$phaseStreaks = Get-MaxStreak -History $PhaseHistory -AllValues $allPhases\n$completedStreaks = Get-MaxStreak -History $CompletedHistory -AllValues $allCompleted\n\n# Classify: INVARIANT if streak >= 3, VARIANT if streak <= 1\n$invariants = @()\n$variants = @()\nforeach ($k in $topicStreaks.Keys) {\n    if ($topicStreaks[$k] -ge 3) { $invariants += $k }\n    elseif ($topicStreaks[$k] -le 1 -and $topicStreaks[$k] -gt 0) { $variants += $k }\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"=== INVARIANT Elements (streak >= 3) ===\"\n$invariants | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  INV: $_ (streak: $($topicStreaks[$_]))\" }\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\nWrite-Host \"=== VARIANT Elements (streak <= 1) ===\"\n$variants | Select-Object -First 15 | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  VAR: $_ (streak: $($topicStreaks[$_]))\" }\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# ── Step 4: Prediction Test ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Test: Given pulse N's invariant set + previous invariant set, \n#       can we predict pulse N+1's invariant set better than random?\n# \n# Metric: Precision = |predicted ∩ actual| / |predicted|\n#         Recall = |predicted ∩ actual| / |actual|\n#         Baseline = random selection of same-size set\n\nWrite-Host \"=== PREDICTION TEST ===\"\nWrite-Host \"Testing: Does current pulse's invariants predict next pulse's invariants?\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# For each consecutive pair (N, N+1), check if N's invariants appear in N+1\n$correct = 0; $total = 0\n$precisionSum = 0; $recallSum = 0\n$baselineCorrect = 0\n\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $States.Count - 1; $i++) {\n    $curr = $States[$i].Raw.Topics\n    $next = $States[$i+1].Raw.Topics\n    \n    # Current invariants in this pulse\n    $currInvariants = $curr | Where-Object { $_ -in $invariants }\n    \n    # Actual overlap with next pulse\n    $overlap = ($currInvariants | Where-Object { $_ -in $next }).Count\n    \n    if ($currInvariants.Count -gt 0) {\n        $precision = $overlap / $currInvariants.Count\n        $recall = if ($next.Count -gt 0) { $overlap / $next.Count } else { 0 }\n        $precisionSum += $precision\n        $recallSum += $recall\n        $correct += $overlap\n        $total += $currInvariants.Count\n    }\n    \n    # Baseline: random element from current\n    if ($curr.Count -gt 0 -and $next.Count -gt 0) {\n        $baselineCorrect += 1  # baseline: ~1/|curr| chance of guessing right\n    }\n}\n\n$avgPrecision = if ($total -gt 0) { $precisionSum * $total / ($total * $total) } else { 0 }\n# Simpler: mean precision per pair where currInvariants > 0\n$pairCount = 0; $sumPrecision = 0; $sumRecall = 0\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $States.Count - 1; $i++) {\n    $curr = $States[$i].Raw.Topics | Where-Object { $_ -in $invariants }\n    $next = $States[$i+1].Raw.Topics\n    if ($curr.Count -gt 0) {\n        $pairCount++\n        $overlap = ($curr | Where-Object { $_ -in $next }).Count\n        $sumPrecision += $overlap / $curr.Count\n        $sumRecall += if ($next.Count -gt 0) { $overlap / $next.Count } else { 0 }\n    }\n}\n\n$meanPrecision = if ($pairCount -gt 0) { $sumPrecision / $pairCount } else { 0 }\n$meanRecall = if ($pairCount -gt 0) { $sumRecall / $pairCount } else { 0 }\n$baselineRate = 0.05  # random baseline: ~5% (few topics, large space)\n\nWrite-Host \"Pairs evaluated: $pairCount\"\nWrite-Host \"Mean Precision: $([math]::Round($meanPrecision * 100, 1))%\"\nWrite-Host \"Mean Recall:    $([math]::Round($meanRecall * 100, 1))%\"\nWrite-Host \"Baseline:       ~$([math]::Round($baselineRate * 100))% (random)\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# ── Step 5: Gap Sensitivity Test ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Hypothesis: The more the pulse content changes (gap), the more invariants collapse\n# Measure: For each gap between consecutive pulses, compute Jaccard similarity\n#          between pulse N's topics and pulse N+1's topics\n\nWrite-Host \"=== GAP SENSITIVITY ===\"\nWrite-Host \"Testing: Do bigger content gaps correlate with invariant collapse?\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n$gapSizes = @()\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $States.Count - 1; $i++) {\n    $t1 = $States[$i].Time\n    $t2 = $States[$i+1].Time\n    $gapMinutes = ($t1 - $t2).TotalMinutes\n    \n    $currTopics = $States[$i].Raw.Topics\n    $nextTopics = $States[$i+1].Raw.Topics\n    \n    $union = ($currTopics + $nextTopics) | Sort-Object -Unique\n    $intersection = ($currTopics | Where-Object { $_ -in $nextTopics })\n    $jaccard = if ($union.Count -gt 0) { $intersection.Count / $union.Count } else { 0 }\n    \n    $gapSizes += @{\n        GapMinutes = [math]::Round($gapMinutes, 1)\n        Jaccard = [math]::Round($jaccard, 3)\n        IntersectionCount = $intersection.Count\n    }\n}\n\n# Group by gap size buckets\n$smallGap = $gapSizes | Where-Object { $_.GapMinutes -le 30 }\n$mediumGap = $gapSizes | Where-Object { $_.GapMinutes -gt 30 -and $_.GapMinutes -le 120 }\n$largeGap = $gapSizes | Where-Object { $_.GapMinutes -gt 120 }\n\n$avgJaccardSmall = if ($smallGap.Count -gt 0) { ($smallGap | Measure-Object -Property Jaccard -Average).Average } else { 0 }\n$avgJaccardMedium = if ($mediumGap.Count -gt 0) { ($mediumGap | Measure-Object -Property Jaccard -Average).Average } else { 0 }\n$avgJaccardLarge = if ($largeGap.Count -gt 0) { ($largeGap | Measure-Object -Property Jaccard -Average).Average } else { 0 }\n\nWrite-Host \"Small gaps (<30 min):   avg Jaccard = $([math]::Round($avgJaccardSmall, 3)) (n=$($smallGap.Count))\"\nWrite-Host \"Medium gaps (30-120m): avg Jaccard = $([math]::Round($avgJaccardMedium, 3)) (n=$($mediumGap.Count))\"\nWrite-Host \"Large gaps (>120 min): avg Jaccard = $([math]::Round($avgJaccardLarge, 3)) (n=$($largeGap.Count))\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# ── Step 6: Phase Persistence Analysis ─────────────────────────────────────\nWrite-Host \"=== PHASE PERSISTENCE ===\"\nforeach ($phase in $allPhases) {\n    $streak = $phaseStreaks[$phase]\n    $cls = if ($streak -ge 3) { \"INVARIANT\" } elseif ($streak -le 1) { \"VARIANT\" } else { \"transitional\" }\n    Write-Host \"  [$cls] '$phase' (streak: $streak)\"\n}\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# ── Step 7: Summary Score ──────────────────────────────────────────────────\nWrite-Host \"=== EXPERIMENT SUMMARY ===\"\n$passPrecision = $meanPrecision -gt $baselineRate\n$passRecall = $meanRecall -gt $baselineRate\n$passJaccard = ($avgJaccardSmall -gt $avgJaccardLarge)  # shorter gaps → more invariant overlap\n\n$score = ($passPrecision ? 1 : 0) + ($passRecall ? 1 : 0) + ($passJaccard ? 1 : 0)\nWrite-Host \"Precision > baseline: $(if ($passPrecision) {'PASS'} else {'FAIL'}) ($(($meanPrecision*100).ToString('N1'))% vs ${baselineRate*100}%)\"\nWrite-Host \"Recall > baseline:    $(if ($passRecall) {'PASS'} else {'FAIL'}) ($(($meanRecall*100).ToString('N1'))% vs ${baselineRate*100}%)\"  \nWrite-Host \"Gap→Jaccard correlation: $(if ($passJaccard) {'PASS'} else {'FAIL'}) (small=$([math]::Round($avgJaccardSmall,2)), large=$([math]::Round($avgJaccardLarge,2)))\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"TIC Score: $score/3\"\n\nif ($score -ge 2) {\n    Write-Host \"VERDICT: SUPPORTED — Structural invariance is predictive. Compression=causal holds.\"\n    $verdict = \"SUPPORTED\"\n} elseif ($score -ge 1) {\n    Write-Host \"VERDICT: PARTIAL — Invariance is weakly predictive. Need richer state representation.\"\n    $verdict = \"PARTIAL\"\n} else {\n    Write-Host \"VERDICT: REJECTED — Structural invariance does NOT predict continuity.\"\n    $verdict = \"REJECTED\"\n}\n\n# ── Step 8: Write results ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\n$results = @\"\n# TIC Experiment Results — $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm\")\n\n## Setup\n- Pulse logs analyzed: $($States.Count)\n- Time range: $($LogFiles[-1].LastWriteTime) → $($LogFiles[0].LastWriteTime)\n- Invariant threshold: streak >= 3 consecutive pulses\n- Variant threshold: streak <= 1\n\n## Invariant Classification\n- Invariant elements (streak >= 3): $($invariants.Count)\n- Variant elements (streak <= 1): $($variants.Count)\n- Key invariants: $($invariants -join ', ')\n\n## Prediction Test\n- Pairs evaluated: $pairCount\n- Mean Precision: $([math]::Round($meanPrecision * 100, 1))%\n- Mean Recall: $([math]::Round($meanRecall * 100, 1))%\n- Random baseline: ~$([math]::Round($baselineRate * 100))%\n- Result: $(if ($passPrecision) {'BETTER THAN RANDOM'} else {'NOT BETTER THAN RANDOM'})\n\n## Gap Sensitivity\n- Small gaps (<30 min) Jaccard: $([math]::Round($avgJaccardSmall, 3))\n- Medium gaps (30-120m) Jaccard: $([math]::Round($avgJaccardMedium, 3))\n- Large gaps (>120 min) Jaccard: $([math]::Round($avgJaccardLarge, 3))\n- Hypothesis (shorter gap → more overlap): $(if ($passJaccard) {'CONFIRMED'} else {'REJECTED'})\n\n## Phase Persistence\n$(foreach ($phase in $allPhases) { \"  $($phase): streak=$($phaseStreaks[$phase])\" })\n\n## TIC Score: $score/3\n## VERDICT: $verdict\n\n## Implications\n- If SUPPORTED: compression=causal hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n- Invariant elements = causal anchors (Phase status, research topic persistence)\n- Gap size can be used to weight reconstruction confidence\n- Next: Use invariants as fixed points in compression, treat variants as contingent details\n\n## Next Experiment\n- Train actual embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- Measure: does cosine similarity between pulse embeddings correlate with Jaccard?\n- Success criteria: >60% next-pulse prediction using only embedding dot products\n\"@\n\n$ResultsPath = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"research\\TIC_RESULTS.md\"\n$results | Out-File -FilePath $ResultsPath -Encoding UTF8\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"Results written to: $ResultsPath\"\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\operations\\tic_experiment.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17780,"output":4808,"cacheRead":11757,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34345,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774274576229}}
